@demographics
go-to: menu

**Demographic Groups**

**Working Class**: The urban working class - blue-collar workers in factories, workshops, mines, and the like. Many are socialist, supporting either the FLP or CP. They make up 40-50% of the population.

**Old Middle**: The old middle class consists of independent artisans, shopkeepers, and small-time businesspeople. They tend to be conservative and are the strongest base for the far right. 10-15% of the population.

**New Middle**: The new middle class consists of white-collar workers and government employees. This is the base of liberalism. 10-15% of the population.

**Rural**: Small and large farmers and independent rural workers. This is the base of the FLP. They have been radicalized by the Depression and the Drought they they remain committed to holding their property. 60-65% of the population.

**Catholics** are the largest religious minority, at about 30% of the population. They disproportionately support the PPS Party (or the Bavarian People's Party in Bavaria).

**Jews** account for between 0.5% to 1% of the population, and tend to support liberal parties, mostly the LPS, although substantial numbers support the FLP or CP.


