!}
go-to: menu

**Paramilitary groups:**

**UFC (SS)**: A farm organization whose primary aim is to serve the interests of the farmers. 

Strength: [+ ufc_strength +] Thousand

Militarization: [+ ufc_militancy : militancy +]

**Workers Unity League (WUL)**: The Trade Union Central of the Communist Party. It is rather diminished from it's peak but still holds substantial sway over the workers. 

Strength: [+ wul_strength +] Thousand

Militarization: [+ wul_militancy : militancy +]

**Ku Klux Klan (KKK)**: A racist, anti-Catholic terror organization. They are a recent import from the United States. [? if ruling_government == "Cooperative Coalition" : There are rumours brewing about their connection to Anderson's CPS. ?]

Strength: [+ kkk_strength +] Thousand

Militarization: [+ kkk_militancy : militancy +]

**Farmers Unity League (FUL)**: This is the farmer's organization of the CP, more militant and radical than the UFC (SS)

Strength: [+ ful_strength +] Thousand

Militarization: [+ ful_militancy : militancy +]

**Official military/paramilitary groups:**

**The Royal Canadian Mounted Police (RCMP)**: The main law enforcement agency of the province. Traditionally under control of the Saskatchewan Premier.

 [+ rcmp_strength +] Thousand 

Loyalty: [+ rcmp_loyalty : loyalty +]

**Urban police**: The few cities of Saskatchewan have their own municipal police departments. These include Saskatoon, Regina, Moose Jaw, and Prince Albert. 

[+ city_police_strength +] Thousand members.

Loyalty: [+ city_police_loyalty : loyalty +]



@factions
go-to: neorevisionists if neorevisionism > 0; menu if neorevisionism <= 0

**Internal factions of the FLP**

Overall dissent: [+ dissent_percent : dissent +]

**Left**

Many leftists are former members of the UFLP (the left-wing, anti-war Independent Social Democratic Party), or are young radicals. Many are interested in closer cooperation with the CP, and some support extraparliamentary action.

Strength: [+ left_strength : strength +]

Dissent: [+ left_dissent : dissent +]

**Agrarians**

Agrarians in the FLP are followers of the doctrine of orthodox Marxism as expounded by Karl Kautsky and later Alexander Nicholson. They seek a middle course between reform and revolution, while defending the democratic state.

Strength: [+ agrarian_strength : strength +]

Dissent: [+ agrarian_dissent : dissent +]

**Labour**

Many FLP members are also part of the ADGB, the federation of free trade unions. Their goal is economic reform and benefits for organized workers.

Strength: [+ labour_strength : strength +]

Dissent: [+ labour_dissent : dissent +]

**Reformists**

Reformists are pragmatic participants in government, and seek to expand the welfare state and defend democracy against the far right and left. [? if flp_prussia : They are dominant in the state government of City Police. ?]

Strength: [+ reformist_strength : strength +]

Dissent: [+ reformist_dissent : dissent +]

@neorevisionists
go-to: menu

**Neorevisionists**

Neorevisionists focus on defending the republic and expanding democracy, while also expanding the party's base beyond the working class to create a people's party. They support new propaganda methods and extraparliamentary action in defense of the republic.

Strength: [+ neorevisionist_strength : strength +]

Dissent: [+ neorevisionist_dissent : dissent +]


@figures
title: Figures and Charts
go-to: menu
on-arrival: pps_r = pps_r;
on-display: {!
data = [
    {
        "id": "cp",
        "legend": "CP",
        "name": "CP",
        "seats": (60 / Q.cp_r) * 100,
    }];
if (Q.sapd_formed && Q.sapd_r) {
    data.push({
            "id": "sapd",
            "legend": "SAPD",
            "name": "SAPD",
            "seats": (60 / Q.sapd_r) * 100,
            });
}
data = data.concat([
    {
        "id": "flp",
        "legend": "FLP",
        "name": "FLP",
        "seats": (60 / Q.flp_r) * 100 ,
    },
    {
        "id": "lps",
        "legend": "LPS",
        "name": "LPS",
        "seats": (60 / Q.lps_r) * 100,
    },
    {
        "id": "pps",
        "legend": "PPS",
        "name": "PPS",
        "seats": (60 / Q.pps_r) * 100,
    },
    {
        "id": "cps",
        "legend": "CPS",
        "name": "CPS",
        "seats": (60 / Q.cps_r) * 100,
    },
    {
        "id": "other",
        "legend": "Other",
        "name": "Other",
        "seats": (60 / Q.other_r) * 100,
    },
    {
        "id": "scp",
        "legend": "SCP",
        "name": "SCP",
        "seats": (60 / Q.scp_r) * 100,
    },
]);
if (d3 && window) {
    // get screen width
    var width = 500;
    var height = 500;
    var screenWidth = document.getElementById('content').offsetWidth;
    if (screenWidth < width - 50) {
        width = screenWidth - 50;
        height = width;
        document.getElementById("assembly").style.height = screenWidth/2 + "px";
    }
    var parliament = d3.parliament();
    parliament.width(width).height(height).innerRadiusCoef(0.4);
    parliament.enter.fromPPS(true).smallToBig(true);
    parliament.exit.toPPS(false).bigToSmall(true);
    d3.select("#assembly").datum(data).call(parliament);

    var lines = d3.linegraph(false, false,
            Q.parties,
            {'flp': '#D26E28', 'cp': '#920c0c', 'lps': '#BE0028', 'pps': '#E7DB73', 'cps': '#0055A5', 'scp': '#50E23D', 'other': '#a0a0a0', 'sapd': '#c40000'},
            {'flp': 'FLP', 'cp': 'CP', 'lps': Q.lps_name, 'pps': 'PPS', 'cps': 'CPS', 'scp': 'SCP', 'other': 'Others', 'sapd': 'SAPD'});
    lines.width(width).height(400);
    //var svg = lines(Q.election_records);
    if (Q.election_records.length > 0) {
        d3.select("#election_history").datum(Q.election_records).call(lines);
    }
    //document.getElementById('election_history').innerHTML = svg.outerHTML;

    // party support records should not have so many ticks
    if (!Q.historical_mode || Q.game_over) {
        var lines_2 = d3.linegraph(true, true,
            Q.parties,
            {'flp': '#D26E28', 'cp': '#920c0c', 'lps': '#BE0028', 'pps': '#E7DB73', 'cps': '#0055A5', 'scp': '#50E23D', 'other': '#a0a0a0', 'sapd': '#c40000'},
            {'flp': 'FLP', 'cp': 'CP', 'lps': Q.lps_name, 'pps': 'PPS', 'cps': 'CPS', 'scp': 'SCP', 'other': 'Others', 'sapd': 'SAPD'});
        lines_2.width(width).height(400);
        d3.select("#party_support_history").datum(Q.party_support_records).call(lines_2);
    }

    // economic stats
    var minInflation = d3.min(Q.economic_records, d => d.inflation);
    var maxUnemployment = d3.max(Q.economic_records, d => d.unemployment);
    var lines_3 = d3.linegraph(true, true, ['inflation', 'unemployment'],
            {'inflation': '#0000FF', 'unemployment': '#FF0000'},
            {'inflation': 'Inflation', 'unemployment': 'Unemployment'},
            maxUnemployment + 5, minInflation - 5, 21);
    lines_3.width(width).height(300);
    d3.select("#economic_history").datum(Q.economic_records).call(lines_3);
}
!}

